  "description": "Dark Thaumaturgy is the name given to Thaumaturgy learned from demons. Vampires may make infernal pacts to gain blood sorcery quickly, paying a steep and variable price tied to the demon bargained with—often considered too high even by other vampires. It is most often practiced by the Baali bloodline and among the Sabbat (notably the Tremere antitribu, credited with developing some of its best-known paths). Beyond offering easier access to common Thaumaturgy, Dark Thaumaturgy includes unique infernal paths and rituals powered by Hell itself, greatly feared and always learned at a price (either a general bargain or a path-specific affliction).",
